#DStv403 CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa delivers the 2023 State of the Nation Address. This year's edition comes amid the worst rolling blackouts on record coupled with the rising cost of living and high unemployment. LIVE BLOG | SONA 2023 The State of the Nation Address is an occasion in which the three arms of the state – the Judiciary, the National Legislature and the Executive – participate as a demonstration of the country’s constitutional dispensation and culture, and to ensure that all three arms are focused on national priorities.